reviews.text: I came here for the first time last night and in all honesty the food was really mid. I got the al pastor, asada, and buffalo chicken tacos. For $4-$5 a taco I would expect it to have higher quality ingredients and great flavor but all three tacos were underwhelming flavor wise. I can see how some people would enjoy eating here but it‚Äôs just not for me.
Wow!!! This is an amazing place. Delicious tacos. Fresh flour tortillas, fresh chips, and fresh salsa!!! The house ranch is crazy good. Definitely get some food here!

There is one item at this restaurant that keeps me coming back and will keep me coming back so long as I live.

You can come to this restaurant and order just about any taco and you will think that the tacos are above normal, but they are not good enough for me to be a repeat customer for the price. One taco however, is a cut above the rest.

The buffalo tacos are out of this world good! The sauce, pickled veggie, handmade tortilla, and fried chicken combo has been perfected.

You must come try this taco!!

Came with coworkers for a lunch around 12:30 and it wasn't as busy as one would think. Which was fine since we were a large party.
As soon as you walk in, there's two kiosks you can place your order at or if you'd rather, go further into the restaurant and place your order with someone.
You look at the menu and prices and wonder how can you get full off off 2 tacos and a side and make it worth it? These aren't your fast food tacos. These are much more than just a shell, meat, lettuce, and cheese.
Everyone got different items off the menu and everyone enjoyed their meals.
I personally got the 2 taco platter which came with a side of choice which I picked the tots. I left satisfied. I got the Korean BBQ pork and Cascabel Chili Chicken. Both were amazing and highly recommend. The tots were topped with sauce and other goodies.
I didn't get pictures of the menus but it's completely different from the pictures I can see online and the link to the menu is an old one.
I would come back again if I'm in the area.

I wasn't Too impressed with this restaurant. For a taco place, I expected a bigger variety of tacos to choose from. What they did offer tasted pretty good. The prices seem reasonable. I was disappointed they didn't have condiments (hot sauces, salt & pepper packets, ect) to go along with the meal.
Overall, this restaurant wasn't the best place I've ever tried.

detailedReviews.author: John Bunderson
detailedReviews.text:
Tip of the hat for creating a fresh savory menu of Asian/Mexican fusion.

The Asian Nachos are a unique experience. The chips are fried wantons, the mock Kimchi substitutes for cheese, and there's a heat that catches you off guard in the opening bites, but finishes smooth as I found myself scraping the bottom of the dish for the final morsels.

The tots are crisp, but be prepared for the Buffalo vinegarette sauce. The bottom tots get saturated by the sauce, there may be a benefit to ordering sauce on the side to keep the tot crisp until the last tots.

The taco experience was neutral as Korean BBQ taco comes with kimchi and onion, that my wife doesn't like, so there wasn't much left on the taco. The second taco was the old skool steak asada and she really liked the flavors.

Malasada are best enjoyed warm, but dipping the donut into the gooey agave glaze requires some engineering to clear a spot for dipping. We both agree a scoop of vanilla ice cream would take this dish to the next level. By itself, still has Great flavor!

Overall a new and interesting experience that may not be for everyone, but I enjoyed our visit tonight.

detailedReviews.author: Josue Gomez C.
detailedReviews.text:
Best staff ever. Kind and helpful. It is a gastronomic experience from over the world.
180 Tacos and Global Street Eats is a fantastic restaurant located in North Provo on University Avenue that serves up some of the best tacos and global street food in the area. The menu is diverse and offers a wide range of flavors and cuisines from around the world.

One of the standout items on the menu is the Korean BBQ tacos, which are packed with tender, flavorful beef and topped with a tangy slaw and spicy Sriracha mayo. The tacos are served on soft corn tortillas and are bursting with flavor in every bite.

Another must-try item is the chicken tikka masala burrito, which combines the classic Indian dish with a Mexican twist. The burrito is packed with juicy chicken, fragrant rice, and a creamy sauce that is both spicy and savory.

The restaurant also offers a range of sides and drinks to round out your meal, including loaded fries, sweet plantains, and refreshing agua frescas.

The staff at 180 Tacos and Global Street Eats are friendly and welcoming, and the service is fast and efficient. The food is made fresh to order and is always delicious.

Overall, 180 Tacos and Global Street Eats is a fantastic restaurant that offers a diverse menu of tasty and unique dishes. Whether you're in the mood for classic street tacos or want to try something new, this restaurant is definitely worth a visit.

detailedReviews.author: David O.
detailedReviews.text: Ever since I tried their buffalo chicken rice bowl, I'm hooked! 180 Tacos and Global Street Eats offers an amazing selection of unique flavors and ingredients that I've never seen before. The portion size is also generous, which is always a plus. Whenever I'm in the mood for something fresh and unique, I always find myself heading to this joint!

I just threw away my meal and went to Chipotle for dinner.

If this was a one time thing I wouldn‚Äôt be leaving a review but I loved this place so much and now the quality is just awful. My wife ordered a steak salad and the lettuce was browning, the meat was again over cooked, and the whole meal was just subpar.

I can see how some people would enjoy eating here but it‚Äôs just not for me.

negative.author: Lindsay Cherrington
negative.text: This place has gone down hill from what it was several years ago. We ordered, then had someone come tell us 15 minutes later that items were unavailable. They brought each person in our groups food out separately with 5-10 minutes between each one. So we basically all ate at different times. Other people who had just sat down were getting their food before us, and we had been waiting forever. So some people in our group went without having any food. Horrible experience. Will not be returning. It‚Äôs unfortunate because we used to love this place.
